gomodel:SYNGO_280  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1 shows that EphB2 and NMDA subunit GluN1 co-associate into a physical complex after heterologous expression and in rat cortex. Activation of EphB2 by aggregated ephrinB-Fc induces interaction and co-clustering of EphB2 with GluN1 in cultured cortical neurons (Fig. 2, 3). Other NMDAR subunits (GluN2A and GluN2B) co-cluster with EphB2 as well (Fig .4).\n\nFig. 6 shows that treatment of cultured neurons with the EphB ligand EphrinB-Fc increases the number of NMDAR containing specializations, and the number of pre- and postsynaptic specializations in cultured neurons.\n\nFig. 7 shows that elevating EphB2 in cultured neurons increases the number of NMDAR clusters along dendrites.. Experimental description: Cortical and hippocampal neurons were made from E17-E19 animals using previously described methods (Xia et al., 1996). Xia et al states use of rats for neuronal culture." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_280" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

